  "title": "feat: handling routing in Next.js",
  "body": "### [FX-1976](https://algolia.atlassian.net/browse/FX-1976)\r\n\r\n- Added 3 new options to `history` router\r\n- Added a check and warning in `react-instantsearch-hooks` if Next.js is detected without the new router\r\n- New package for the router, along with e2e tests\r\n\r\nAbout the e2e tests : \r\n\r\nI decided to put them inside of the package itself rather than in `tests/e2e` because it's very specific. For now it's only local because I'm not sure how to approach CI with those, I don't think we should run them for any commit.\r\nAlso I edited the `next` example so I could test more but if you think it should be a separate example like `next-routing` I will do it !\n\n[FX-1976]: https://algolia.atlassian.net/browse/FX-1976?atlOrigin=eyJpIjoiNWRkNTljNzYxNjVmNDY3MDlhMDU5Y2ZhYzA5YTRkZjUiLCJwIjoiZ2l0aHViLWNvbS1KU1cifQ",
